<subSubSection id="C3086569FFBFFF9AE1AF21A0BB91FB7D" pageId="19" pageNumber="220" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BAD36E2FFBFFF9AE1AF21A0BB91FB7D" blockId="19.[151,1437,402,1153]" pageId="19" pageNumber="220">
<materialsCitation id="3B7A3CBFFFBFFF9AE1AF21A0BB91FB7D" ID-GBIF-Occurrence="1499315587" country="Brazil" location="Solimoes River" municipality="Penera River" pageId="19" pageNumber="220" specimenCount="1" stateProvince="Amazonas">
<emphasis id="B966EAF0FFBFFF9AE1AF21A0BB46FC0D" bold="true" box="[199,315,984,1009]" pageId="19" pageNumber="220">Remarks.</emphasis>
Eurides Furtado (private collection, Appendix) provided photographs of two females seemingly of 
<taxonomicName id="4C124D61FFBFFF9AE1FF2184BB50FBE8" box="[151,301,1020,1044]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Bia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="220" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="rebeli" subSpecies="cuprea">
<emphasis id="B966EAF0FFBFFF9AE1FF2184BB50FBE8" box="[151,301,1020,1044]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="220">rebeli cuprea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingCountry id="F3057672FFBFFF9AE01C2184BBC6FBE9" box="[372,443,1020,1045]" name="Brazil" pageId="19" pageNumber="220">Brazil</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingRegion id="49D6F800FFBFFF9AE0A12185B83FFBE9" box="[457,578,1021,1045]" country="Brazil" name="Amazonas" pageId="19" pageNumber="220">Amazonas</collectingRegion>
, Maués (
<collectingMunicipality id="6BC9AC98FFBFFF9AE3C12185B93EFBE9" box="[681,835,1020,1045]" pageId="19" pageNumber="220">Penera River</collectingMunicipality>
). Note that the examined material includes one male and two females from the Amazonian municipality of Manacapuru, which extends north and south of the 
<location id="8ECD6039FFBFFF9AE45C2658BAA5FBA1" LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:03BB87F4FFBFFF9AE1FF235FBB91FB7D:8ECD6039FFBFFF9AE45C2658BAA5FBA1" country="Brazil" municipality="Penera River" name="Solimoes River" pageId="19" pageNumber="220" stateProvince="Amazonas">Solimões River</location>
. Although we find it less likely that 
<taxonomicName id="4C124D61FFBFFF9AE3EE263DB93DFBA0" box="[646,832,1092,1116]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Bia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="220" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="rebeli" subSpecies="cuprea">
<emphasis id="B966EAF0FFBFFF9AE3EE263DB93DFBA0" box="[646,832,1092,1116]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="220">B. rebeli cuprea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was collected north of the Solimões, this should be confirmed in future fieldwork.
</materialsCitation>
</paragraph>
